<A NAME="MKfancysurf"></A>
<H2><IMG SRC="../Pics/new.jpg" ALT="">
MKfancysurf.sl</H2><P>
OK, take Larry's <A HREF="../LGShaders#LG_orennayar">LG_orennayar</A> shader, turn it into a function, add rim-lightting, and transparency, then you have <B>MKfancysurf</B>.  This shader was inspired from thinking about the illumination controls that have been talked about for Pixar's, <B>A Bug's Life</B>  The RIB uses 
<A HREF="#MKshadowdistant_rim">MKshadowdistant_rim</A>
and
<A HREF="#skinbump">skinbump</A>
<P><B>NOTE:</B>  FYI -- Beware that the Oren-Nayar lighting model is mathematically, unstable around the 90degree illuminance cone-angle. -- Tal.
<P>
